1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,212
ALL CHARACTERS, ORGANIZATIONS,
LOCATIONS, AND INCIDENTS

2
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:48,965
DEPICTED IN THIS DRAMA
ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,844
"Cleared of suspicion. Not guilty."

4
00:00:54,512 --> 00:00:56,806
This case has reignited the debate
over reform

5
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:59,392
of the police and prosecution's
investigative authority.

6
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:01,478
Removal of the restriction line
did not cause the accident.

7
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:03,938
The lawyer who got special treatment at
the Eastern District Prosecutors' Office,

8
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:04,981
what was his name?

9
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,566
It's Oh Ju-seon.

10
00:01:06,649 --> 00:01:08,151
But now, a former judge is involved

11
00:01:08,234 --> 00:01:09,652
for someone who just cut a rope.

12
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,197
A Police-Prosecution Council
will be formed soon.

13
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,908
We need someone who will protect
our authority at all costs.

14
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:17,869
And it should be an officer who works
in the field, not at headquarters.

15
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:18,870
You want me to do that?

16
00:01:18,953 --> 00:01:22,499
In 2017, a police sergeant
committed suicide in Dongducheon.

17
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:25,126
Do you know anything about
the Segok Police Station?

18
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:26,503
"Segok"?

19
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:29,380
If you want Si-mok and me
to work on this together…

20
00:01:29,464 --> 00:01:31,341
I mean, I'll do fine alone.

21
00:01:31,424 --> 00:01:34,594
You brought it to our office,
so we should take care of it.

22
00:01:38,056 --> 00:01:41,518
EPISODE 3

23
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:52,237
All right, I'm here.

24
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:54,656
-You can bring out the food now.
-Sure.

25
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,827
Were you giving him a hard time?

26
00:01:58,910 --> 00:02:00,245
We were having a good time.

27
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:04,666
You look like you've spent your whole life
reading in your room.

28
00:02:04,749 --> 00:02:07,335
Do you feel as if
you're looking in the mirror?

29
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:09,254
-Assistant Chief Kim Sa-hyun.
-I'm Hwang Si-mok.

30
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:12,924
He's two years my junior,
but we joined the prosecution together.

31
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:14,342
Yes, I'm aware.

32
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:26,771
This is fresh omasum
with sesame seed oil drizzled on top.

33
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:28,898
You can have it raw. It's on the house.

34
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:31,734
They specialize in horumon,
dishes made from innards.

35
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:34,529
Mr. Hwang,
you're lucky to have such an amazing boss.

36
00:02:34,612 --> 00:02:37,532
Thanks to him, you can enjoy
these incredibly fresh delicacies.

37
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:38,449
Right.

38
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:49,794
We're cooking this well-done
because you've never had it before.

39
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:50,712
Thank you, sir.

40
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:52,922
Do you usually eat well?

41
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:55,800
I'm sure he does.
What is he going to do, starve to death?

42
00:02:56,634 --> 00:02:57,719
You look so shy.

43
00:02:58,636 --> 00:03:00,847
Can you eat alone at a restaurant?

44
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:02,181
Why the hell not?

45
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:03,349
Don't you worry.

46
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:06,269
Also, do you really think he's shy?

47
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,228
Give me a break.

48
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:25,330
I'm okay, sir.

49
00:03:32,962 --> 00:03:34,881
All right, here's to our success.

50
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:36,382
Cheers!

51
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:50,438
-Try it when it's slightly cooked.
-Yes, sir.

52
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:57,487
Goodness, he really has no idea
how to eat this.

53
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:01,908
Add a bit of wasabi in the ponzu sauce
and dip the meat in it.

54
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:05,036
Add a little more wasabi.

55
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:23,596
All right.

56
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,516
Chief Woo's eldest kid
got into an international middle school.

57
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:27,850
Right.

58
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:29,727
And his daughter is
a classical ballet prodigy.

59
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,105
Prodigy, my ass.
She's costing me a fortune.

60
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:34,691
It's costing you because she has talent.

61
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:37,944
I have no idea what my daughter will be
when she grows up.

62
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:41,364
Don't you want to get married?

63
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:42,782
Don't. Why go down that path?

64
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:45,118
I wish you had given me that advice.

65
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:46,786
Why didn't you talk me out of it?

66
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:47,954
Why did you give up on me?

67
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:50,581
Hey, I've given up on myself.
Who am I to dissuade anyone?

68
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:55,670
Do you have alcohol intolerance?

69
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:59,048
-No, sir.
-Then what? Can you drink?

70
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:00,216
Well…

71
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:39,255
Hello!

72
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,548
Hello.

73
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,467
Isn't she Han Yeo-jin?

74
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:48,056
-Hello.
-Hello, it's good to see you.

75
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:50,725
-Hello.
-Hello.

76
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:53,269
Hey, what's up?

77
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:56,564
My goodness.

78
00:05:56,647 --> 00:05:58,316
Gosh, you didn't have to.

79
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:00,985
You're not a guest.
You didn't have to bring anything.

80
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:03,696
Let's see.

81
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:06,866
-Hold on. What about rice?
-I got fried rice.

82
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:08,993
You sure know the drill.

83
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:10,244
-Detective Jang.
-Yes?

84
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:11,829
Spare me a moment.

85
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:13,247
-But the food…
-Come on.

86
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:16,167
-We should eat the fried rice right away.
-I'll be quick.

87
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,293
What's going on?

88
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,298
-Me?
-Yes!

89
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:24,592
Come on.

90
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:26,385
I won't.

91
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:29,514
The Police-Prosecution Council? Forget it.

92
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:31,099
Come on, just do it.

93
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:33,309
Take the captain.
He'd be perfect for the job.

94
00:06:33,392 --> 00:06:35,728
No, he doesn't qualify because of his age.

95
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:36,938
There's an age limit?

96
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:40,483
"The movement to redistribute
the investigative authority

97
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:44,028
is led by Police University graduates who
wish to take over the entire police force.

98
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:46,489
In the past, the police weren't able
to effectively reason

99
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:49,158
with prosecutors
who are legal specialists.

100
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,661
But the elite officers
who graduated from the Police University

101
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:54,455
have reignited the conflict
between the prosecution and police.

102
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:57,083
The Police University graduates
are the ones pulling the strings!"

103
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,293
We weren't able to reason with them?

104
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,337
That's what
all the prosecutors are saying.

105
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,630
So they're saying this happened

106
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:05,174
because the Police University graduates
are pulling our strings?

107
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:07,593
Damn it. Look who's talking!

108
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,429
The prosecution is ruled by
graduates from specific colleges.

109
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:12,098
That's what I'm saying!

110
00:07:12,181 --> 00:07:14,809
You should show them that
you're not under control.

111
00:07:14,892 --> 00:07:18,104
You can join the council even if
you're not a Police University graduate.

112
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:21,315
The only thing is that
low-ranking officers can't join.

113
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:24,485
Think about it. If it's a patrol officer
or a senior patrol officer,

114
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:27,989
-the prosecution will outrank us.
-But what has age got to do with it?

115
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,075
This is just between you and me.

116
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:34,912
I don't think the chief wants someone
who's older than her.

117
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,664
Will it make her uneasy?

118
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:39,417
To have a subordinate
who's older than her?

119
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:42,837
She's saying it has to be someone
who's at least a lieutenant,

120
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,089
but not a Police University graduate.

121
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:47,633
Just think. A lieutenant
who's not a Police University graduate?

122
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:50,803
Then we're talking well over 40.
I can't find anyone in their 30s.

123
00:07:51,929 --> 00:07:53,014
This reminds me of someone.

124
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:54,640
Who?

125
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:57,018
You and the captain.

126
00:07:57,977 --> 00:07:59,479
He's older than you, but…

127
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:02,356
I mean, he's way older than you.

128
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,025
But you outrank him,

129
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:05,443
so you've beaten him.

130
00:08:06,068 --> 00:08:07,778
Cut it out.

131
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,530
Jeez, I'm not doing this!

132
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:11,824
Come on!
Are you really going to be like this?

133
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:15,953
Do you know who popped into my head
when I was talking to Chief Choi?

134
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:18,539
The man who is a detective
with the title of lieutenant.

135
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,000
He's only in his 30s
and he's good at his job.

136
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:23,794
Had I not known you,
I couldn't have thought of this.

137
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:26,255
-Right?
-Jeez.

138
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:29,467
Come on. I'm not that good.

139
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:34,639
But you know,
it's not something I can decide on my own.

140
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:36,015
I need the captain's permission.

141
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:37,975
He'll let you do it, of course.

142
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:40,770
-Him?
-Yes, sir.

143
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:44,273
-Where are you taking him?
-The Police-Prosecution Council.

144
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,441
But why?

145
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:48,027
As a representative of
the investigative officers. How about it?

146
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:51,906
No, you can't.

147
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:53,824
Why not?

148
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,327
Hey, we're already short-staffed.

149
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:57,912
We lost you already, and him too?

150
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:59,789
Look at us. What are we going to do?

151
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:01,999
But Detective Jang isn't leaving us
for good.

152
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,918
-He'll only attend their meetings, right?
-Yes!

153
00:09:04,001 --> 00:09:07,046
We can hire someone if he's gone for good.

154
00:09:07,129 --> 00:09:09,465
It'll be like having a ghost on the team.

155
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:13,344
Also, they'll take him
whenever they need him.

156
00:09:13,427 --> 00:09:16,973
But it'd be good to have a field officer
occupying a seat in the council.

157
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:19,016
Those who do fieldwork

158
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,270
may be able to present different views
to those who sit at their desks all day.

159
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:23,563
Whose side are you on?

160
00:09:24,897 --> 00:09:25,773
-Hey.
-Yes, sir.

161
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:29,485
Take this one. He's friendly,
and he's got a lot of energy.

162
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:31,028
He'll be much better than Geon.

163
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:32,863
Take him.

164
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,116
Sun-chang, how many years has it been
for you?

165
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:36,742
Me? I joined the force three years ago.

166
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:38,160
You punk.

167
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,037
Gosh, you still have a long way to go.

168
00:09:40,121 --> 00:09:41,747
Forget it, then!

169
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:45,167
The suspect will be
at the agency in Bogwang-dong.

170
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:47,211
At ten o'clock, but it may change.

171
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:48,879
-Okay, we're on it!
-What's going on?

172
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:51,090
What? Are you investigating
a real estate fraud?

173
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:52,216
With the Intelligence Unit?

174
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,927
It started out as an assault case,
but he's got a new specialty now.

175
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:55,970
-What?
-Rental scam.

176
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,733
What? Are you coming too?

177
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,610
Pardon?

178
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,325
-Detective Jang!
-Okay.

179
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:46,604
I'll see you again.

180
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:58,741
Gain as much experience as possible.
It'll become a valuable asset.

181
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:00,993
-Pardon?
-It'll be helpful for you,

182
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:04,330
and also for the entire police force.
It's a rare opportunity.

183
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:07,166
Don't you think
real changes will be made this time?

184
00:11:07,249 --> 00:11:10,002
The public supports us,
and the higher-ups are pushing for it.

185
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:13,756
If you join the council and make them
hand over the authority to us,

186
00:11:14,465 --> 00:11:16,217
the three syllables of your name…

187
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,844
I mean, the two syllables of your name
will go down in history.

188
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:21,013
It will look great on your resume too.

189
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:23,849
I'll work extra hard to fill in for you.

190
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,851
So don't worry and just join the council.

191
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:28,813
You're the second one
they're taking from us,

192
00:11:28,896 --> 00:11:30,439
so they'd better let us hire someone.

193
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:32,608
Gosh, I told you
that I'm not leaving the team.

194
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:34,527
Why are you trying to send me away?

195
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:37,696
Hey, do you think Yeo-jin came to us
because she couldn't find anyone else?

196
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:39,949
She doesn't have it as easy as you think.

197
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:42,201
Think about how lonely she must've been.

198
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:45,663
She probably needed someone
she could open up to.

199
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:47,456
Darn it.

200
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:49,792
I'd go if I were ten years younger.

201
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:54,004
-I guess you've lost your vigor.
-No, it's not about that.

202
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:55,548
I didn't go to the Police University.

203
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:57,716
I should've at least
built connections like that.

204
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,635
I'm deeply regretting it now, okay?

205
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:05,057
-Hey, Jang Geon.
-Yes, sir.

206
00:12:05,141 --> 00:12:08,185
I'm sure you want more than just having
your own team and staying a lieutenant.

207
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:10,521
Just make sure

208
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,898
you bring Yeo-jin with you
when you're done.

209
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:15,985
That's all I ask for.

210
00:12:16,735 --> 00:12:18,529
Luck is obviously not on my side.

211
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,615
Had I served as an expert member,
I would've been able to transfer

212
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:23,409
to the Central District
Prosecutors' Office.

213
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:25,911
It would've been amazing.

214
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:31,083
Why get rid of it when it was my turn
to be sent to the National Assembly?

215
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,294
Everyone got promoted.
Why rob me of the opportunity?

216
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:36,630
Who knows? They might give you
special treatment to make up for it.

217
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:38,716
Just do a good job with this.

218
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:41,677
I always do a good job.
Did I ever do a bad job?

219
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,471
This time, you must do especially well.

220
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:45,598
Our lives are on the line.

221
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:51,187
Hey, give me a list of every assemblyman
who used to be a prosecutor.

222
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,938
-Former judges too.
-Yes, sir.

223
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:00,821
-Oh, boy.
-Let's also find out how many assemblymen

224
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:02,198
used to be in the police force.

225
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:07,369
The police came up with another proposal
on police autonomy.

226
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:08,704
-Let's get that too.
-Yes, sir.

227
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:10,789
Get a separate report on Jeju.

228
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:12,708
Compare it with the older ones
for the meeting…

229
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:15,085
Right,
you have to be there tomorrow morning.

230
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:17,546
-Where?
-You don't need to know.

231
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,840
We don't have time.
Get on it as soon as you're back.

232
00:13:38,025 --> 00:13:39,568
He doesn't even smoke?

233
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:43,072
Hey.

234
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,366
Do you have a lighter?

235
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:49,078
Darn it. Would they have one
at the cash register?

236
00:13:49,161 --> 00:13:51,705
What's the matter?
Are you worried about something?

237
00:13:52,289 --> 00:13:53,123
What?

238
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:57,670
Joining us for a smoke?

239
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,547
No. I'll get going, sir.

240
00:14:00,297 --> 00:14:01,507
Go where?

241
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:04,468
I've never seen anyone leave
before their seniors do.

242
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:05,386
Oh, I see.

243
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:07,596
I'll see you tomorrow, sir.

244
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,892
Hey!

245
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,443
2019 PROPOSAL
FOR AUTONOMOUS POLICE SYSTEM

246
00:15:04,695 --> 00:15:06,155
PROSECUTOR HWANG SI-MOK

247
